trend_summary: 2000-2020 imagery shows steady suburban infill. West-side office parks expanded block by block, replacing grass lots. Strip-commercial buildings and parking appeared along the highway. Central golf course and lakes stayed intact, while scattered forest eastward shrank slightly as new housing clusters emerged. Overall built surface rose moderately but green space still dominates.
notable_changes: Incremental expansion of office/industrial blocks in the northwest quadrant.
New retail/parking complexes built parallel to the southbound highway.
Small residential enclaves added on the eastern forest edge.
Minor forest clearance and conversion to lawn or construction staging areas.
Road-network widening and new roundabouts improving internal circulation.
